    "body": "Just to be clear, the general rule we want is: _\"if the level indexer is a scalar, collapse the level, otherwise keep the level\"_. Correct?\n\nThis should then also hold for levels that are not up front?\n\nSo this\n\n```\nIn [42]: df.loc[(slice(None), 2), :]\nOut[42]:\n     c\na b\n1 2  3\n```\n\nwould give\n\nSo \n\n```\nIn [42]: df.loc[(slice(None), 2), :]\nOut[42]:\n   c\na\n1  3\n```\n"
